          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two separate experiments were  performed at the Los",
                "Alamos Neutron Science Center at LANL using incident",
                "proton energies of 100 and 200MeV. In each experiment,",
                "the original beam energy was degraded to approximately",
                "half of its original value using aluminum degraders."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Natural thorium foils of 99.7% purity were used in",
                "the experiment. The foils were of 2.5mm x 2.5mm",
                "approximate dimensions, with mass thicknesses ranging",
                "from 60.5 to 70.5 g/cm2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "MONITOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": null,
                "reaction": {
                  "code": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-22,,SIG",
                  "code_unit": [
                    {
                      "unit": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-22,,SIG",
                      "field": {
                        "reaction": "13-AL-27(P,X)11-NA-22",
                        "target": "13-AL-27",
                        "projectile": "P",
                        "process": "X",
                        "product": "11-NA-22",
                        "quantity": ",SIG",
                        "data_type": null,
                        "general_quantity_modifier": null,
                        "quantity_236": ",SIG"
                      }
                    }
                  ],
                  "unit_combination": "(%)"
                }
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Aluminum foils of 99.9%",
                "purity and 65mg/cm2 thickness were used as beam",
                "fluence monitors"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Thorium foils irradiated for nuclear reaction",
                "cross section measurements were counted on an ORTEC",
                "GEM10P4-70 p-type Al-windowed detector with relative",
                "efficiency of 10% at 1333 keV and a measured FWHM of",
                "1.99 keV at 1333 keV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Activation method was used. Irradiated foils",
                "were counted over a period of approximately 12 months,",
                "collecting approximately 300 spectra"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A sequence of chromatographic separations was",
                "developed to isolate Pa isotopes from the irradiated",
                "Th target and subsequently remove fission and other",
                "activation products. In the first step, Pa was",
                "isolated from the bulk Th mass via anion exchange in",
                "hydrochloric acid media. In the second step sample",
                "was divided in two similarly sized target portions",
                "were dissolved and two slightly different methods of",
                "anion exchange were performed with each portion.",
                "After the anion exchange step, the respective Pa",
                "fractions were collected and subjected to extraction",
                "chromatography."
              ]
            }
          ],
